<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-286-730  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 286 730.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  May 22 1989 n249 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Microsoft installs fiber net. (Fiber Distributed Data Interfacenetwork)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Haight, Timothy.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Microsoft Corp recently installed the first enterprise-widecorporate backbone network based on the emerging Fiber DistributedData Interface (FDDI) standard.andP;  The network, installed by theUngermann-Bass Inc subsidiary of Tandem Computers Inc, servesthree computer centers and five buildings.andP;  It will be expandedwithin the year to link 20 Ethernet local area networks in 12Microsoft buildings.andP;  This will involve connectivity with morethan 4,500 nodes, including microcomputers, terminals and IBM andDEC host computers.andP;  FDDI networks are dual-ring, token-passing,optical fiber networks.andP;  Microsoft found itself with a heavilyused network that was getting too busy to move the mass ofinformation required for their operation.andP;  Because of the dangerof installing a new technology as a main network, Microsoft hasdouble-ring redundancy as well as a backup Ethernet link.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Microsoft Corp. (data processing)Tandem Computers Inc. (contracts)Ungermann-Bass (contracts).andO;Ticker:    MSFT; TDM.andO;Topic:     American National Standards InstituteLocal Area NetworksFiber Distributed Data Interface StandardFiber OpticsBridges (Connector)SalesTechnology.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>